<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Teens Dead After Garage Fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOORE, Okla. (AP) -- Two teen-age sisters and a young friend were found dead
Wednesday after a flash fire in a sealed garage room in their suburban Oklahoma
City home, police said.
</P>
<P>
	   Investigators found a can of gasoline spilled in the room and a small
electric space heater, police Sgt. Scott Singer said.
</P>
<P>
	   Firefighters, who had to use a key to get into the room, found the bodies of
Fallon Brown, 16, her sister, Brandi, 13, and friend Shelly Franklin, 12.
</P>
<P>
	   ``It is thought that the space heater may have ignited the concentrated gas
fumes that created a flash fire, killing the girls,'' Singer said. The fire
apparently ``snuffed itself out due to a lack of oxygen or explosive force
confined in the small space.''
</P>
<P>
	   The Brown girls' mother called police about 4:30 p.m. after arriving home
and smelling smoke and being unable to find her daughters, he said.
</P>
<P>
	   Fire investigators were still at the scene late Wednesday, and an autopsy
was planned to determine the causes of the girls' deaths, Singer said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
