<HEADLINE> Seahawks Hire Sidwell for Defense  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SEATTLE (AP) -- Steve Sidwell was hired Wednesday as defensive coordinator
of the Seattle Seahawks, coach-general manager Mike Holmgren said.
</P>
<P>
	   Sidwell, 55, arrives with a three-year contract to fill the gap left by the
death of defensive coordinator Fritz Shurmur, who arrived with Holmgren from
Green Bay but was diagnosed with cancer and left the team last summer.
</P>
<P>
	   An 18-year league veteran, Sidwell was defensive coordinator for the New
England Patriots the last two years under Pete Carroll, who was fired the day
after New England ended n 8-8 season.
</P>
<P>
	   "Steve is a good coach with a strong system and has had a great deal of
success in the NFL," Holmgren said in a release.
</P>
<P>
	   Before his tenure with the Patriots, Sidwell joined the Green Bay staff in
1995 as linebackers coach under Holmgren, but left before the start of the
season to become defensive coordinator for the Houston Oilers.
</P>
<P>
	   "I'm glad I have a second chance to add Steve to my coaching staff,"
Holmgren said.
</P>
<P>
	   Sidwell was defensive coordinator for the New Orleans Saints from 1986
through 1994. He previously was a defensive line coach with Indianapolis and
linebackers coach with the Patriots.
</P>
<P>
	   Defensive assistant Bob Zeman announced his retirement Wednesday. He came
out of retirement in 1999 to assist the Seahawks' defensive coaching staff after
Shurmur's death. Zeman handled linebackers for the Seahawks.
</P>
<P>
	   "Bob Zeman was enjoying the good life of retirement and did a personal favor
to me this season," Holmgren said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
