<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Russia's Buryatia Region  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW (AP) -- A magnitude-five earthquake hit Russia's Buryatia region
overnight, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   No casualties or damage were reported from the temblor, which struck near a
village on the eastern shore of Lake Baikal, 2,400 miles east of Moscow.
</P>
<P>
	   Buryatia, whose western border is defined by the lake, also sits on the
northern frontier of Mongolia. It is the site of frequent earthquakes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
