<HEADLINE> 'Puffy' Hires Two Top Lawyers  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Sean "Puffy" Combs has hired two top lawyers -- Johnnie
Cochran and Benjamin Brafman -- to help him beat charges of fleeing a nightclub
shooting with an illegal weapon, newspapers report.
</P>
<P>
	   Cochran, O.J. Simpson's ex-lawyer, and Brafman, who defended Mob killer
Salvatore "Sammy the Bull" Gravano, reportedly joins Harvey Slovis on the
defense team of the millionaire music mogul.
