<HEADLINE> Dow Up 71.05; Nasdaq Up 54.96  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mostly higher today as a report of relatively
modest inflation boosted the bond market and calmed a jittery stock market.
Investors remained fairly cautious in the hours ahead of a speech by Federal
Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan.
</P>
<P>
	   With an hour remaining in Wall Street's regular session, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 71.05 at 11,622.15.
</P>
<P>
	   Broader stock indicators were also slightly higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index was up 16.63 at 1,448.88, and the Nasdaq composite index was up 54.96
at 3,904.98.
