<HEADLINE> European Stock Prices Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- European stocks rose Thursday, but London shares were
slightly dampened by the Bank of England's interest rate increase, which did
nothing to alleviate global fears of inflation and expectations for European
rate rises this year.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 313 shares in companies in
countries that joined the single currency, rose 3.61 points to 401.88. The Dow
Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index rose 39.1 points to 4688.4.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 606 shares in European companies was 1.91
points, or 0.6 percent, higher at 354.83, while the Dow Jones Stoxx 50 Index
rose 30.9 points to 4494.3.
</P>
<P>
	   In domestic markets, London's FTSE-100 Share Index closed almost flat, down
1.3 points at 6531.5; Frankfurt's Xetra DAX Index rose 43.17 points or 0.6
percent to 6955.98; the Paris CAC-40 Index gained 50.74 points or 0.9 percent to
5633.24; and Milan's MIBTEL Index was 208 points or 0.8 percent higher at
27,711.
</P>
<P>
	   In Germany, a sharp gain in Siemens shares along with selected financial
stocks lifted the index. Investors scrambled for Siemens shares before the
stock-market listing of its semiconductor subsidiary Infineon.
</P>
<P>
	   Also in Frankfurt, automaker BMW closed down 2.8 percent after a board
member told a German newspaper that its British unit Rover may post losses for
1999 of 1.8 billion marks (about $1 billion).
</P>
<P>
	   In London, the Bank of England's decision to raise interest rates by a
quarter percentage point to 5.75 percent had little downward effect on shares.
The announcement had been expected and had been written into trading already.
</P>
<P>
	   Shares in Cable &AMP; Wireless gained after the company said it had bought eight
independent European internet companies.
</P>
<P>
	   In France, the long-awaited signing of defense-to-media group Lagardere with
pay-TV channel Canal Plus lifted shares. Lagardere shares rose 7.1 percent on
heavy trade, while Canal Plus shares closed up 9.2 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
