<HEADLINE> Authorities in New Jersey arrest suspect in Holyoke shootings  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
    	   HOLYOKE, Mass. (AP) - A man suspected of fatally shooting two Holyoke
men and wounding a 4-year-old child has been arrested in New Jersey.
<P>
	   Ramon Santana, 25, was captured in Jersey City, N.J., on Wednesday
afternoon, police said. He was held without bail pending arraignment in Hudson
County Superior Court in New Jersey on fugitive charges.
</P>
<P>
	   A spokeswoman for the Hampden County District Attorney's office said
Thursday it was not immediately clear when Santana might be returned to
Massachusetts.
</P>
<P>
	   Arrest warrants were issued for Santana last Friday on two counts of murder
and one count of attempted murder in connection with the Jan. 3 fatal shootings
of Gregory Cantela, 23, and Abraham Candelario, 27, and the wounding of
Cantela's 4-year-old son, who has not been identified.
</P>
<P>
	   The boy, who was shot in the chest, was released from Baystate Medical
Center in Springfield on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   Massachusetts law enforcement officials tipped off Jersey City police that
Santana, who previously lived in New Jersey, might be in their area, the
Springfield Union-News reported. Officials said Santana had a relative living
there.
</P>
<P>
	   The shootings come on the heels of a difficult time for Holyoke.
</P>
<P>
	   Police officer John DiNapoli was shot to death Dec. 22. In August, a church
and much of a city block burned in a downtown fire. Two juveniles were later
charged with arson in connection with the fire.
</P>
<P>
	   Two rallies have been planned to unite the community and spread an
anti-violence message.
</P>
<P>
	   One was to be held Friday, and the second on Monday, Martin Luther King Day.
</P>
</TEXT>
