<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thursday, Jan. 13, 2000
</P>
<P>
	   Gates Names Ballmer Microsoft CEO
</P>
<P>
	   REDMOND, Wash. (AP) -- Microsoft chairman and founder Bill Gates
today promoted longtime friend and president Steve Ballmer to chief
executive officer of the software giant. Gates, who has turned over
much of the day-to-day operations of Microsoft to Ballmer over the
past year and a half, will remain chairman but will also take the
title, ``chief software architect.'' He said he was taking the
action so he could return ``to what I love most -- focusing on
technologies for the future.'' Microsoft stock was up 2 at 107
13/16 today.
</P>
<P>
	   Boeing Buying Hughes Satellite Unit
</P>
<P>
	   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Hughes Electronics Corp., one-time maker of
airplanes and spy satellites, today made a $3.75 billion cash deal
to sell its satellite-building unit business to Boeing Co. and
focus on entertainment and Internet services. The pact turns Boeing
into the world's biggest commercial satellite maker, and allows
Hughes executives to pursue their goal of becoming a dominant
player in the world of high-speed wireless communications. ``Boeing
intends to be No. 1 in space,'' said said Phil Condit, Boeing
chairman and chief executive officer. Analsyts found little to
criticize in the deal, which meshes Hughes' expertise in satellite
hardware with Boeing's Delta and SeaLaunch rocket programs. Boeing
stock was down 11/16 at 42 3/8 today.
</P>
<P>
	   Dow Closes at New High 11,582.43
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks rose today after a report of relatively
modest inflation boosted the bond market and calmed jittery stock
investors. Financial shares led the Dow Jones industrials to a new
closing record. The Dow rose 31.33 to close at 11,582.43, just past
its previous record of 11,572.20. Broader stock indicators also
closed higher. The Nasdaq composite index broke out of a two-day
slump to finish up 107.24 at 3,957.26. Stocks rose after the Labor
Department said inflation remained under control in 1999.
</P>
<P>
	   Financial Figures
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:
Dow Industrials:        11,582.43  + 31.33
