<HEADLINE> Pfizer Likely To Win Warner-Lambert  </HEADLINE>
    By PHIL GALEWITZ AP Business Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Pfizer Inc. emerged Thursday as the likely winner in the
high stakes battle for rival drugmaker Warner-Lambert Co.
</P>
<P>
	   Two months after agreeing to merge with American Home Products Corp.,
Warner-Lambert executives bowed to investor pressure and said they would
negotiate a buyout from Pfizer instead.
</P>
<P>
	   Pfizer has been trying to break up the marriage of its two competitors since
the day they announced their stock swap deal on Nov. 4.
</P>
<P>
	   Pfizer's counter-offer for Warner-Lambert was higher from start and the gap
