<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-13 18:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Recommends 3 for Iraq Post  </HEADLINE>
   By NICOLE WINFIELD Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   UNITED NATIONS (AP) -- Secretary-General Kofi Annan asked Security Council
members Thursday to consider three candidates to head the new weapons inspection
agency or come up with other names themselves, officials said.
</P>
<P>
	   Annan met for about an hour with the ambassadors of Russia, China, France,
Britain and the United States in a bid to get their approval for an executive
chairman for the U.N. Monitoring, Verification and Inspection Commission, or
UNMOVIC.
</P>
<P>
	   Annan proposed Sweden's U.S. ambassador and the former chief U.N. weapons
inspector Rolf Ekeus; Brazil's former U.N. ambassador, Celso Amorim; and
Finland's ambassador to Israel and Cyprus, Pasi Patokallio, according to the
Chinese deputy ambassador.
</P>
<P>
	   Annan asked the permanent five members of the council to report back Friday
on whether any of the three were agreeable, and to propose other names for
consideration, said the deputy Chinese ambassador, Shen Guofang.
</P>
<P>
	   UNMOVIC was formed last December to replace the U.N. Special Commission,
known as UNSCOM, which was charged after the 1991 Persian Gulf War with
uncovering Iraq's efforts to develop weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
	   UNSCOM inspectors pulled out of Baghdad in December 1998, ahead of U.S. and
British airstrikes.
</P>
<P>
	   Ekeus was UNSCOM's first executive chairman. He left the post in 1997 to
become Sweden's ambassador to the United States, and was replaced by the
outspoken Australian arms expert Richard Butler, who stepped down in June.
</P>
<P>
	   Amorim chaired three special U.N. panels earlier this year on Iraq's
disarmament, the humanitarian situation in the country, and the issue of Kuwaiti
prisoners of war and reparations from the Gulf War. He is currently Brazil's
ambassador to the United Nations in Geneva.
</P>
<P>
	   Patokallio was director for nonproliferation and arms control affairs in
Finland's Foreign Ministry from 1994-95 before becoming the ministry's deputy
director general for political affairs.
</P>
<P>
	   Annan was to consult Friday with the 10 nonpermanent members of the council.
Under the U.N. resolution that created UNMOVIC, he must select an executive
chairman by Sunday. If no consensus can be reached by then, he may ask the
council for a delay, Shen said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
