<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miniature Skateboards Recalled  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- A teddy bear company and a toy retailer are recalling
about 15,500 miniature-skateboard key chains because their wheels may come off,
posing a choking risk to young children.
</P>
<P>
	   The key chains came attached to Z.Z. Jamboarder teddy bears, which were
produced by the Vermont Teddy Bear Co. of Shelburne, Vt. The toy bears were sold
nationwide by Zany Brainy of King of Prussia, Pa., through their stores, catalog
and Web site.
</P>
<P>
	   The companies have had two reports of wheels coming off, but no reports of
injuries, the Consumer Product Safety Commission said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   The Z.Z. Jamboarder teddy bear is light brown, about 15 inches long and
wears a white shirt, jeans, a purple hat and sunglasses. A sewn-in tag under the
bear's left arm reads ``Z.Z. Jamboarder'' on one side and ``Limited Edition
1999'' on the other.
</P>
<P>
	   The skateboard key chain is about 4 inches long with red wheels and is
attached to a loop on the right side of the bear's jeans. It bears an emblem of
a bear head in a red circle.
</P>
<P>
	   Zany Brainy sold the bears with key chains last year between November and
December for $10 to $13 with the purchase of $50 of other merchandise.
</P>
<P>
	   The safety commission advises consumers to take the skateboard key chains
away from young children immediately and return them to any Zany Brainy store to
receive a bean-filled animal toy. The bear and key chain can also be returned
for a refund.
</P>
<P>
	   For more information, consumers can call the Vermont Teddy Bear Co. toll
free at 1-877-293-2327 between 8:30 a.m. and 10 p.m. EST Monday through Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
