<HEADLINE> Crash Closes Calif. Freeway  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PERRIS, Calif. (AP) -- Twenty cars and trucks collided Thursday in
chain-reaction accidents on a fog-shrouded stretch of freeway. Several minor
injuries were reported.
</P>
<P>
	   It began about 5:40 a.m. when a car rear-ended a tractor-trailer on
Interstate 215 about 70 miles southeast of Los Angeles, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
	   By the time officers arrived, several other accidents occurred in the area,
said Veronica Gonzalez, spokeswoman for the California Highway Patrol. Dense fog
and speed likely contributed to the crashes, she said.
</P>
<P>
	   ``People just don't slow down and they tailgate,'' Gonzalez said.
</P>
<P>
	   The southbound lanes of the freeway were closed for about three hours.
</P>
</TEXT>
