<HEADLINE> Results From Poll on Democrats  </HEADLINE>
   By The Associated Press
<TEXT>
<P>
	   Some results from a new poll that show the mixed signals the public is
giving about the Clinton administration and Al Gore, vice president and
Democratic presidential front-runner. When results don't total 100 percent, the
remainder either didn't know or refused to answer.
</P>
<P>
	   Are you better off than you were eight years ago?
</P>
<P>
	   -- Yes, better off, 73 percent
</P>
<P>
	   -- No, not better off, 19 percent
</P>
<P>
	   -- Same or other, 8 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   (President Clinton's job approval was at 63 percent, nearly nine-out-of-10
Democrats feel that way)
