<HEADLINE> Davis To Chair Gore Calif. Campaign  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Gov. Gray Davis will serve as state chairman of
Vice President Al Gore's presidential campaign, Gore announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   Helping Gore with the March 7 primary and, if he wins the Democratic
nomination, the November election, ``is Davis' No. 1 political priority this
year,'' said Davis' political consultant, Garry South, who will advise the Gore
campaign.
</P>
<P>
	   South was credited with helping Davis win a long-shot bid for governor in
1998.
</P>
<P>
	   ``Whether improving education, protecting our environment or expanding
economic opportunities for working families, every time I have called on Al Gore
to take action on behalf of Californians, he has acted,'' Davis said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
	   ``I want to continue working with an administration in Washington that
understands the unique needs of this state and is willing to work with us to
address them.''
</P>
<P>
	   Davis formally endorsed Gore in September.
</P>
</TEXT>
