and remained the nation's only undefeated Division I team as the seventh-ranked
Orangemen beat South Carolina 77-74 in overtime. Ryan Blackwell had six points
and two steals in overtime for Syracuse (13-0). Blackwell, who made only two
3-pointers all season, and Jason Hart connected from long range in the final
minute for a 59-57 lead.
</P>
