<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-13 23:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No. 17 LSU 82, Arkansas 69  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) -- LSU coach Sue Gunter won her 600th game Thursday
night as DeTrina White had 27 points and 12 rebounds in the 17th-ranked Tigers'
82-69 victory over Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
	   Gunter, who has a 600-269 record in 36 seasons, is the fourth coach to reach
600 victories in the women's game, after Texas' Jody Conradt, Tennessee's Pat
Summitt and Rutgers' Vivian Stringer.
</P>
<P>
	   LSU (12-3, 3-1 Southeastern Conference) led throughout the first half, but
Arkansas (9-5, 0-2) halved a 12-point deficit by halftime.
</P>
<P>
	   "I'm just glad to have this 600th win and have it over with," Gunter said.
"I was more worried about getting win No. 12 for the season and win No. 3 in SEC
play than 600. The game has been very gracious to me, and I'm very thankful for
what the game has given me."
</P>
<P>
	   LSU held a 10-point lead with 10:37 to play, but the Lady Tigers couldn't
shake Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
	   The Lady Razorbacks took a 67-66 lead on a jumper by Brandi Whitehead with
4:32 to play. Arkansas' Wendi Willits hit a 16-footer at the 3:54 mark for a
69-68 lead, but LSU then held the Lady Razorbacks without a point the rest of
the way, finishing with a 13-0 run.
</P>
<P>
	   White, who was 12-of-14 from the field, had 12 points in the opening 11:29.
</P>
<P>
	   LSU's Marie Ferdinand scored 14 of her 20 points in the second half, and
Katrina Hibbert finished with 16.
</P>
<P>
	   Willits led Arkansas with 25 points, including 6-for-8 shooting from 3-point
range, and Dana Cherry scored 12 points.
</P>
<P>
	   LSU forced 20 turnovers that led to 18 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
