<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-13 23:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dennis Conner Out of America's Cup  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   AUCKLAND, New Zealand (AP) -- America True ended Dennis Conner's America's
Cup challenge on Friday when it beat Stars and Stripes by 1 minute, 32 seconds
in the last race of the semifinal series.
</P>
<P>
	Stars and Stripes needed to beat America True to force a sailoff on Saturday
with Prada, which it trailed by a point in the standings. Both boats finished
with 7-3 records in the 10-race semifinals, but Stars and Stripes had a point
deducted for using an illegal rudder in a previous race.
</P>
<P>
	AmericaOne, which clinched a spot in the challenger finals two days ago and
finished the semifinal series with an 8-2 record, will face Prada in a best-of-9
challenger final beginning Jan. 25.
</P>
<P>
	The winner will face Team New Zealand for the America's Cup beginning Feb. 19.
</P>
<P>
	It was only the second victory in 10 starts for America True, which moved to
fifth place in the semifinal series with the victory. Le Defi Francais, also
with a 2-8 record, finished last after having half a point deducted for causing
a collision with Stars and Stripes in a previous race.
</P>
<P>
	Japanese syndicate Nippon finished fourth with a 4-6 record.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
